Sung suggests pet owners take brief breaks every hour, to spend a few minutes playing with their animals, whether it’s throwing a ball or working with them on learning a new trick.
“I think everybody should have an emergency plan for their pets, especially living in the Bay Area, which is an epicenter of natural disasters,” Sung said.